
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `loffice` baraye ejra kardan LibreOffice, yek suite office baz-matn va raygan, estefade mishavad. Shoma mitavanid barnamehaye mokhtalef LibreOffice ra ba in dastoor baz konid, mesle Writer (baraye neveshtan), Calc (baraye hesabdari), va Impress (baraye araye).

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `loffice --writer`  --> 📝 Baz kardan Writer (barnameh neveshtari)
    🔹 `loffice --calc`  --> 🧮 Baz kardan Calc (barnameh hesabdari)
    🔹 `loffice --impress` --> 🖼️ Baz kardan Impress (barnameh araye)
    🔹 `loffice file.odt`  --> 📂 Baz kardan yek file khas ba LibreOffice.  Agar file `odt` bashad ba Writer baz mishavad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ loffice --writer

    🔹 Baz kardan barnameh Writer.

    $ loffice --calc my_data.ods

    🔹 Baz kardan file `my_data.ods` ba barnameh Calc.  Age file mojood nabashe, Calc baz mishe vali file jadid baz nemishe.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ loffice report.odt

    🔹 Agar file `report.odt` mojood bashad, Writer an ra baz mikonad. Agar file mojood nabashad, Writer baz mishavad vali file jadidi ijad nemishavad.


===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `loffice` command is used to launch LibreOffice, a free and open-source office suite. You can use this command to open various LibreOffice applications, such as Writer (for word processing), Calc (for spreadsheets), and Impress (for presentations).

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `loffice --writer`  --> 📝 Open Writer (word processor)
    🔹 `loffice --calc`  --> 🧮 Open Calc (spreadsheet application)
    🔹 `loffice --impress` --> 🖼️ Open Impress (presentation application)
    🔹 `loffice file.odt`  --> 📂 Open a specific file with LibreOffice. If the file is `.odt`, it will open with Writer.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ loffice --writer

    🔹 Opens the Writer application.

    $ loffice --calc my_data.ods

    🔹 Opens the `my_data.ods` file with the Calc application. If file doesn't exist, Calc opens without creating the file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ loffice report.odt

    🔹 If `report.odt` exists, Writer opens it. If the file does not exist, Writer opens without creating a new file.
